WEBVTT

00:01.234 --> 00:03.204
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Okay, let's do this, peeps.

00:03.237 --> 00:04.338
After breakups and make-ups,
 Jane the Virgin

00:04.372 --> 00:06.374
finally got engaged to Michael.

00:06.407 --> 00:08.742
Will you marry me? Marry me!
Yes! Yes!

00:08.776 --> 00:12.546
And her baby daddy Rafael,
 well, he said he'd try

00:12.580 --> 00:15.549
to accept it, maybe because he
 had other things on his mind.

00:15.583 --> 00:18.452
See, his ex-wife Petra
 just gave birth to twins.

00:18.486 --> 00:21.089
Elsa and Anna.
Like in Frozen?

00:21.122 --> 00:22.490
No one except for you
would think of that.

00:22.523 --> 00:23.557
Oh, and he recently learned

00:23.591 --> 00:25.059
his mother was a crime lord.

00:25.093 --> 00:26.827
I know, cray-cray, right?

00:26.860 --> 00:28.496
Even crazier,
 he was working with Michael

00:28.529 --> 00:30.631
to find his long-lost brother.

00:30.664 --> 00:32.165
Derek Ruvelle, son of Rafael's

00:32.200 --> 00:33.634
mother Elena Di Nola.

00:33.667 --> 00:35.103
Our buddy Derek
disappeared the day after

00:35.136 --> 00:36.837
Mutter's identity
was discovered.

00:36.870 --> 00:38.839
I know, straight out
 of a telenovela, right?

00:38.872 --> 00:41.442
Well, imagine this--
 Jane's father,

00:41.475 --> 00:44.312
international telenovela star
 Rogelio de la Vega

00:44.345 --> 00:46.114
was kidnapped
 by his biggest fan.

00:46.147 --> 00:48.849
And even worse, he's in a fight
 with his family.

00:48.882 --> 00:51.185
I just think I need
some space right now.

00:51.219 --> 00:52.586
So they aren't even
 that worried!

00:52.620 --> 00:54.388
Such bad luck, right?

00:54.422 --> 00:56.324
And speaking of, Alba

00:56.357 --> 00:57.758
had been corresponding
 with her first lover,

00:57.791 --> 01:00.794
the notorious
 Pablo Alonso Segura.

01:00.828 --> 01:02.730
And Xo invited him for a visit.

01:06.667 --> 01:10.138
And I got to say I really hope
 that's not true, don't you?

01:12.340 --> 01:14.308
Breaking news--

01:14.342 --> 01:17.678
our Jane Gloriana Villanueva
 always had strong opinions.

01:17.711 --> 01:19.613
I'm embarrassed
to be from Florida.

01:19.647 --> 01:21.182
About politics.

01:22.483 --> 01:24.485
Too revealing-- change!

01:24.518 --> 01:26.220
Her mother's wardrobe.

01:26.254 --> 01:28.222
Jane, no!

01:31.192 --> 01:33.361
And her grandmother's
 superstitions.

01:33.394 --> 01:35.429
Stop, that's ridiculous.
 Ay!

01:38.766 --> 01:41.135
And I don't want to mistake
 correlation for causation,

01:41.169 --> 01:44.838
but here we are today.

01:44.872 --> 01:49.177
Six weeks away from our Jane
 marrying the man of her dreams.

01:52.313 --> 01:55.149
I'm working on it.
I'm working on it.

01:55.183 --> 01:56.517
I know what you're thinking.

01:56.550 --> 01:58.186
That we've been here
 before, right?

01:58.219 --> 02:00.188
But this time was different.

02:00.221 --> 02:01.789
This time there were
 no reservations.

02:01.822 --> 02:03.824
Did you make the reservations
for the chair rentals?

02:03.857 --> 02:05.493
No, I'm finalizing
the head count.

02:05.526 --> 02:07.561
Michael's brother's a no,
so that's 25.

02:07.595 --> 02:09.763
No, 26-- both his parents
are driving down.

02:09.797 --> 02:13.301
Seriously? Aren't they, like,
archenemies or something?

02:13.334 --> 02:15.769
Well, they're not in a comic
book, but yes, basically.

02:15.803 --> 02:17.305
They haven't been
in the same room

02:17.338 --> 02:18.672
since Michael's
high school graduation.

02:18.706 --> 02:20.808
He's freaking out.
Well, you never know.

02:20.841 --> 02:22.943
I mean, engagements
bring people together.

02:22.976 --> 02:25.713
Michael's parents,
Alba and Pablo.

02:28.616 --> 02:32.253
Ah, yes, Pablo Alonso Segura.

02:32.286 --> 02:33.554
The man,

02:33.587 --> 02:35.556
the myth, the legend.

02:35.589 --> 02:37.258
Abuela, you're gonna have to,

02:37.291 --> 02:40.694
because he's traveling
from Venezuela.

02:43.597 --> 02:45.299
You're being ridiculous.
Now, back to the list.

02:45.333 --> 02:47.835
The only question mark
is... Dad.

02:47.868 --> 02:49.337
He still hasn't
gotten back to you?

02:49.370 --> 02:50.404
No.

02:50.438 --> 02:52.573
I'm calling him again.

02:52.606 --> 02:53.674
(phone autodials)

02:53.707 --> 02:54.942
LOLA:
Hello?

02:54.975 --> 02:56.444
Hey, Paola.

02:56.477 --> 02:58.546
Just trying to get in touch
with my dad.

02:58.579 --> 03:00.348
I'm sorry, Jane.

03:00.381 --> 03:01.949
He just stepped into a meeting

03:01.982 --> 03:04.685
with a very important
casting director.

03:04.718 --> 03:07.421
He'll be tied up for a while.

03:07.455 --> 03:09.723
(sighs)
Have him call me back.

03:09.757 --> 03:11.359
Tell him that it's important.

03:11.392 --> 03:13.561
You know what?
Tell him

03:13.594 --> 03:14.928
I'm marrying Michael.

03:14.962 --> 03:18.299
You got it. I'll
give him that message.

03:18.332 --> 03:19.567
(beep)

03:19.600 --> 03:21.569
If you don't call...

03:21.602 --> 03:23.704
she'll know something's wrong.

03:23.737 --> 03:24.805
No!

03:24.838 --> 03:25.973
You can't call!

03:26.006 --> 03:27.641
Stop arguing with me!

03:27.675 --> 03:29.977
You'll say good-bye
to them tonight...

03:31.545 --> 03:34.348
...when we livestream
our murder-suicide.

03:35.883 --> 03:37.385
Okay, if he doesn't respond,

03:37.418 --> 03:38.552
then there's something
definitely wrong.

03:38.586 --> 03:39.653
Something is definitely wrong.

03:39.687 --> 03:40.754
God, this is frustrating!

03:40.788 --> 03:43.591
Thank you for taking Mateo.

03:43.624 --> 03:47.261
I should go-- I don't want
to be late for my new advisor.

03:47.295 --> 03:48.862
Stop. She's gonna love you.

03:48.896 --> 03:52.433
I got to be frank-- last thing
I wanted is another advisee.

04:00.408 --> 04:02.443
I hear you.

04:02.476 --> 04:04.378
A-And I'm sorry
to be adding to your schedule.

04:04.412 --> 04:05.879
Yeah, and apparently,

04:05.913 --> 04:08.782
you wanted a new advisor
because of some complications

04:08.816 --> 04:10.518
with your old one?

04:10.551 --> 04:11.785
That's one way to put it.

04:15.523 --> 04:17.024
Well, life is complicated.

04:17.057 --> 04:19.593
B-But it's all material, right?

04:19.627 --> 04:20.761
That's the clichÃ©.

04:20.793 --> 04:22.496
So, what do you write?

04:22.530 --> 04:25.333
Well, uh, my genre is romance.

04:25.366 --> 04:26.467
(quietly):
Barf.

04:26.500 --> 04:27.768
Did she just say...

04:27.801 --> 04:29.803
Ex-Excuse me, what was that?

04:29.837 --> 04:33.073
I said "barf."

04:33.106 --> 04:35.275
*

04:43.851 --> 04:46.520
So, you're not a fan of romance.
Good to know. (chuckles)

04:46.554 --> 04:48.556
But I do hope
you keep an open mind.

04:48.589 --> 04:51.559
My mind is always open.
Well, I was...

04:51.592 --> 04:52.826
Careful, Jane,
 you're running out

04:52.860 --> 04:54.462
of English Department
 faculty members.

04:54.495 --> 04:55.996
Just as long as it passes
the Bechdel test, okay?

04:56.029 --> 04:57.398
Got it. Yes.
You've heard of it?

04:57.431 --> 04:58.399
No. No, I haven't.

04:58.432 --> 04:59.867
It's a three-part question.

04:59.900 --> 05:02.736
Does the work feature
two female characters...

05:02.770 --> 05:04.738
with names...

05:04.772 --> 05:07.941
who talk about something
other than a man?

05:07.975 --> 05:09.677
Like, for instance,
you, Jane,

05:09.710 --> 05:11.512
talking to me,
Professor Donaldson,

05:11.545 --> 05:13.681
about the work--
that passes the test.

05:14.915 --> 05:17.751
But you, Jane,
talking to me, Marlene,

05:17.785 --> 05:20.388
about your former advisor,
Jonathan Chavez--

05:20.421 --> 05:22.523
that doesn't pass the test.

05:23.724 --> 05:25.526
Oh, yeah, well...

05:25.559 --> 05:27.528
I mean, m-my work
certainly passes the test.

05:27.561 --> 05:29.563
Translation:
 Jane will certainly check

05:29.597 --> 05:31.632
to make sure her work
 passes the test.

05:31.665 --> 05:34.101
(laughs):
Great! Because otherwise...

05:34.134 --> 05:35.803
barf.

05:39.540 --> 05:40.841
Just a little spit-up.

05:40.874 --> 05:42.376
You're okay, Anna.

05:42.410 --> 05:43.977
(Elsa crying)

05:44.011 --> 05:46.947
Hey, Petra,
can you...?
Sure.

05:46.980 --> 05:50.083
(electronic ding)
No, no, no, I meant
can you just pick her up?

05:50.117 --> 05:51.952
Oh, no, it's fine.
I needed water.

05:51.985 --> 05:54.388
Hi. Elsa's
crying again.

05:54.422 --> 05:56.657
And, um, I needed water,
room temperature.

05:56.690 --> 05:59.427
Again, that's not
what the button is for.

05:59.460 --> 06:01.729
But anyway,
I have some good news.

06:01.762 --> 06:04.465
Dr. Grove says you're
getting out today.

06:04.498 --> 06:04.932
What?

06:05.966 --> 06:07.034
I-I thought I, um,

06:07.067 --> 06:08.068
I needed to stay longer

06:08.101 --> 06:09.537
because of my platelet problem.

06:09.570 --> 06:11.605
Things look better.
You're good to go.

06:11.639 --> 06:12.940
The babies, too?

06:12.973 --> 06:15.075
Yes. The babies, too.

06:15.108 --> 06:17.545
Petra...

06:17.578 --> 06:19.079
don't worry, we can do this.

06:19.112 --> 06:21.048
JANE:
 It's gonna be okay.

06:21.081 --> 06:22.716
Michael, I promise.

06:22.750 --> 06:25.018
(sighs): Oh, I don't know.
The last time my parents

06:25.052 --> 06:26.620
were together,
it was a disaster.

06:26.654 --> 06:28.889
There was fighting,
finger-pointing, tears--

06:28.922 --> 06:30.591
mostly mine, but still...
(laughs)

06:30.624 --> 06:32.926
Come on, they are not gonna
do that in front of me.

06:32.960 --> 06:35.162
That's because
the only thing
they can agree on

06:35.195 --> 06:37.698
is how much they love you.

06:37.731 --> 06:38.966
Which is why you
can't leave the room.

06:38.999 --> 06:40.568
I won't leave.
No, I'm serious.

06:40.601 --> 06:41.735
Not even to go
to the bathroom.

06:41.769 --> 06:42.736
Well, I might have
to go to the bathroom.

06:42.770 --> 06:44.438
Remember that astronaut
that put the diaper on?

06:44.472 --> 06:46.206
Stop it. (laughs)
Where's your commitment?

06:46.239 --> 06:49.543
No, I'm serious.
Oh.
(doorbell rings)

06:49.577 --> 06:51.512
Hi, Mom.

06:51.545 --> 06:52.946
Hi, Dad.
Hey.

06:52.980 --> 06:54.748
Hi!

06:54.782 --> 06:55.816
Oh, Jane. Hi.

06:56.850 --> 06:58.552
I didn't realize
you'd be here.

06:58.586 --> 07:00.220
Oh. W-Well, I wanted to see you.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.622
Come on in.

07:01.655 --> 07:04.692
Mike, we were
hoping for a...

07:04.725 --> 07:06.660
private moment alone.

07:07.795 --> 07:10.464
We have some
important family business

07:10.498 --> 07:11.865
we want
to discuss.

07:11.899 --> 07:13.834
Oh. Well, it's just Jane.

07:13.867 --> 07:16.136
I'm just gonna tell her
whatever you say anyway.

07:16.169 --> 07:17.705
MRS. CORDERO:
Fine.

07:17.738 --> 07:19.139
We think you're
making a mistake.

07:19.172 --> 07:20.741
Don't marry her.

07:20.774 --> 07:21.642
Barf.

07:27.715 --> 07:30.584
You... you don't want
Michael to marry me?

07:30.618 --> 07:32.720
You were heartbroken, Mikey.
Don't you remember?

07:32.753 --> 07:34.888
When we found out the two
of you were back together,

07:34.922 --> 07:37.157
I called your father.
We got to talking.

07:37.190 --> 07:39.126
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 At least Jane's
 still bringing them together.

07:39.159 --> 07:41.261
We wanted to reach out, but
then the next thing we knew,

07:41.294 --> 07:43.731
we were getting an evite
to an engagement party.

07:43.764 --> 07:46.099
That's enough.
That's enough.
Michael... it's okay.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.901
You guys should talk.

07:47.935 --> 07:50.170
Um... I'll see you later.

07:51.304 --> 07:53.173
(clears throat
softly)

07:53.206 --> 07:55.175
I am so sorry.
You should not be leaving.

07:55.208 --> 07:57.144
They should be leaving.
I'll kick them out.

07:57.177 --> 07:59.880
No, no, no, don't do that.
Go back inside-- you know,

07:59.913 --> 08:01.582
the longer you're out here,
the worse it'll be,

08:01.615 --> 08:03.083
because then they'll
think I'm upset.

08:03.116 --> 08:04.217
You are upset.

08:04.251 --> 08:06.219
No, no, I'm not.

08:06.253 --> 08:08.856
Just go back inside
and talk to them.

08:08.889 --> 08:10.524
Oh, yeah, and remind your mom

08:10.558 --> 08:11.859
about the time
we got mani-pedis,

08:11.892 --> 08:13.627
and a smoothie,
and we split an Orange Zinger,

08:13.661 --> 08:15.763
and she said that I felt like
the daughter that she never had,

08:15.796 --> 08:17.798
and make it seem like
I told you that at the time

08:17.831 --> 08:19.232
because I was so touched,
and not today, okay?

08:19.266 --> 08:20.601
Okay, go. Go.

08:20.634 --> 08:22.102
PETRA:
 Honestly, go.

08:22.135 --> 08:24.605
We'll be fine.
I was planning
on staying over.

08:24.638 --> 08:26.273
I've got it covered.

08:26.306 --> 08:28.275
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Well, Helga has it covered.

08:28.308 --> 08:29.843
And Wilma.

08:29.877 --> 08:32.279
Well, I guess
you could sit in here

08:32.312 --> 08:34.081
with Helga and Wilma
all night.

08:35.982 --> 08:37.684
(laughs)

08:37.717 --> 08:40.520
See? They think
it's silly, too.

08:47.961 --> 08:50.598
Heard you've
been looking for me.

08:52.766 --> 08:54.234
The cops send you?

08:54.267 --> 08:55.936
No.

08:55.969 --> 08:58.606
But they do want
to talk to you.

08:58.639 --> 09:01.074
I went to prep school
with a topflight attorney.

09:01.108 --> 09:03.176
I'll let him know.
Good.

09:03.210 --> 09:06.814
Okay, look, man, this isn't
about the cops, okay?

09:06.847 --> 09:08.616
Up until a few months ago,

09:08.649 --> 09:10.618
I didn't even know
I had a brother.

09:10.651 --> 09:12.152
Did-did you know?

09:12.185 --> 09:15.022
About me?
No.

09:15.055 --> 09:17.190
Okay.

09:17.224 --> 09:20.093
I mean, so, can... can
we at least just talk?

09:20.127 --> 09:21.629
Maybe.

09:21.662 --> 09:23.330
I'll be in touch.

09:23.363 --> 09:25.332
I'm staying here, by the way.

09:25.365 --> 09:27.701
Mind if I send you the bill...

09:27.735 --> 09:29.302
brother?

09:29.336 --> 09:32.105
(door closes)

09:32.139 --> 09:33.340
You'll meet him in public.

09:33.373 --> 09:35.108
Don't go off with him alone.

09:35.142 --> 09:36.644
Okay, I got it.

09:36.677 --> 09:38.679
(beeps twice)

09:38.712 --> 09:39.847
Oh.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.849
I... I should go.

09:41.882 --> 09:44.818
It's, uh... Jane.

09:44.852 --> 09:46.253
Yeah. Never not awkward.

09:46.286 --> 09:47.955
Maybe once Mateo's in college.

09:47.988 --> 09:49.256
Let me know when you see him.

09:49.289 --> 09:51.258
(smacks lips)
Okay.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.360
(beep)

09:53.393 --> 09:55.829
(sighs)
Hi.

09:55.863 --> 09:57.197
Jane, look, I'm so sorry.

09:57.230 --> 09:58.999
I don't care
what my parents say.

09:59.032 --> 10:00.934
No, no, no, it's not that.
Well, I mean,

10:00.968 --> 10:02.269
it's definitely that,
too, but...

10:02.302 --> 10:03.704
I'm worried about my dad.

10:03.737 --> 10:05.005
I left him a message
this morning,

10:05.038 --> 10:06.273
and I told him
that we were engaged,

10:06.306 --> 10:07.741
and he hasn't
called me back all day.

10:07.775 --> 10:09.142
And we want
to go check in on him,

10:09.176 --> 10:10.744
but he told us
to give him his space.

10:10.778 --> 10:12.079
Okay, I'll-I'll
swing by the condo

10:12.112 --> 10:13.413
and see what's
going on with him.

10:13.446 --> 10:15.115
Thank you. I love you.

10:15.148 --> 10:16.884
He's gonna go check on him.

10:16.917 --> 10:18.118
Good. I feel better.

10:18.151 --> 10:19.720
Hey, can you move

10:19.753 --> 10:21.021
those papers?
Pablo will be here any minute.

10:21.054 --> 10:24.391
Yeah, sure. Sorry.
I was just making sure

10:24.424 --> 10:27.194
that my chapters passed
the Bechdel test.

10:29.930 --> 10:31.899
Yeah, she sounds
like a hard-ass.

10:31.932 --> 10:34.234
Have you had any movement
with Michael's parents?

10:34.267 --> 10:36.436
No, and I'm
so frustrated,

10:36.469 --> 10:38.371
because I love him so much.

10:38.405 --> 10:41.174
(buzzer sounds)
But I don't know
how to prove that to them.

10:41.208 --> 10:42.710
(groans)

10:42.743 --> 10:43.711
Look who it is.

10:43.744 --> 10:45.245
Finally.
 Okay, good.

10:45.278 --> 10:47.247
Bechdel test, take two.

10:47.280 --> 10:49.182
Why aren't you dressed? Pablo's
gonna be here any minute.

10:49.216 --> 10:51.952
(buzzer sounds)
 Geez, this thing is tough.

10:58.926 --> 11:01.929
Ma, stop being
ridiculous.

11:08.902 --> 11:09.870
(both chuckle)

11:19.880 --> 11:23.383
Fine. What's
the undeniable proof?

11:29.422 --> 11:31.859
Afterwards, we will
consider sending him away.

11:33.861 --> 11:36.029
(sighs)

12:27.547 --> 12:29.917
JANE:
 Abuela, there are,
 like, 100 different

12:29.950 --> 12:32.219
environmental factors that
go into an early frost.

12:39.126 --> 12:40.327
(doorbell rings)
(gasps)

12:40.360 --> 12:41.795
He's here!
Come on, Abuela.

12:41.829 --> 12:43.296
No, no, no, no, no. Dame.

12:53.841 --> 12:55.876
Please
come in.

12:55.909 --> 12:58.545
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Okay, this could
 totally be explained

12:58.578 --> 13:00.547
by a fuse blowing
 or a power outage.

13:00.580 --> 13:02.082
(gasps)
 Or is it...

13:02.115 --> 13:04.985
the Curse
 of Pablo Alonso Segura?

13:11.058 --> 13:13.060
It's just our house. The other
houses on the street have power.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.302
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Not entirely true.

13:23.470 --> 13:26.306
Good question.
Let me go check on her.

13:32.312 --> 13:33.446
Stop.

13:33.480 --> 13:34.915
It's not a curse.

13:34.948 --> 13:36.116
You're being silly.

13:37.951 --> 13:40.353
Yes. And you're being rude.

13:40.387 --> 13:42.622
Now, that nice man travelled
a long way to see you

13:42.655 --> 13:44.624
and, yes, maybe
we shouldn't have invited him,

13:44.657 --> 13:46.493
but I read those chats,

13:46.526 --> 13:49.496
and you certainly wrote
pretty vividly

13:49.529 --> 13:51.498
about wanting to see him.

13:51.531 --> 13:54.634
So I'm gonna need you to come
out of this room right now.

13:54.667 --> 13:57.237
And I would change
because he's fine.

14:02.509 --> 14:05.345
Just one more minute.

14:05.378 --> 14:07.948
It'll be quick,

14:07.981 --> 14:09.349
painless,

14:09.382 --> 14:12.152
and when our death goes viral,

14:12.185 --> 14:13.453
we'll be famous.

14:13.486 --> 14:15.222
And they'll make a movie
about us,

14:15.255 --> 14:17.490
maybe.
 At this point, Rogelio's life

14:17.524 --> 14:20.060
actually did start
 to flash before him.

14:20.093 --> 14:22.229
*

